title: shap.image_plot(shap_values) not working
body:
Hello everyone, I'm a newbie in AI and I will try to plot shap value with my data and model.

#Preview_code
-----------------
Here is code explain shap 

def f(x):
   tmp = x.copy()
   preprocess_input(tmp)
   return best_model(tmp)

masker = shap.maskers.Image("inpaint_telea", X_train_255_no_float[0].shape)
explainer = shap.Explainer(f, masker, output_names=labels_text)
shap_values = explainer(X_train_255_no_float[1:3], max_evals=100, batch_size=50, outputs=shap.Explanation.argsort.flip[:4])
shap.image_plot(shap_values)

---------------------
#My_code_and_API
---------------------
Type of data and label in API is numpy.ndarray and list 
I try convert my data and lable same the API but it not working.

Source API is: https://shap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/example_notebooks/image_examples/image_classification/Image%20Multi%20Class.html
